-- Istanbul Consumer Prices Fell 0.61 Percent in June, Chamber Says
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-07-01T11:54:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-01/istanbul-consumer-prices-fell-0-61-percent-in-june-chamber-says.html
Consumer prices in Istanbul fell a
monthly 0.61 percent in June, the city’s chamber of commerce
said.  Annual inflation accelerated to 10.63 percent from 10.57
percent in May, the chamber said in an e-mailed statement today.
Wholesale prices in  Turkey ’s biggest city decreased a monthly
1.18 percent in June, it said.  The statistics office in Ankara is due to publish national
inflation data for June on July 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
